26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_clk_pllgt215.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:33 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "pll.h"
30
31#include <subdev/bios.h>
32#include <subdev/bios/pll.h>
33
34int
35gt215_pll_calc(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev, struct nvbios_pll *info,
36 u32 freq, int *pN, int *pfN, int *pM, int *P)
37{
38 u32 best_err = ~0, err;
39 int M, lM, hM, N, fN;
40
41 *P = info->vco1.max_freq / freq;
42 if (*P > info->max_p)
43 *P = info->max_p;
44 if (*P < info->min_p)
45 *P = info->min_p;
46
47 lM = (info->refclk + info->vco1.max_inputfreq) / info->vco1.max_inputfreq;
48 lM = max(lM, (int)info->vco1.min_m);
49 hM = (info->refclk + info->vco1.min_inputfreq) / info->vco1.min_inputfreq;
50 hM = min(hM, (int)info->vco1.max_m);
51 lM = min(lM, hM);
52
53 for (M = lM; M <= hM; M++) {
54 u32 tmp = freq * *P * M;
55 N = tmp / info->refclk;
56 fN = tmp % info->refclk;
57
58 if (!pfN) {
59 if (fN >= info->refclk / 2)
60 N++;
61 } else {
62 if (fN < info->refclk / 2)
63 N--;
64 fN = tmp - (N * info->refclk);
65 }
66
67 if (N < info->vco1.min_n)
68 continue;
69 if (N > info->vco1.max_n)
70 break;
71
72 err = abs(freq - (info->refclk * N / M / *P));
73 if (err < best_err) {
74 best_err = err;
75 *pN = N;
76 *pM = M;
77 }
78
79 if (pfN) {
80 *pfN = ((fN << 13) + info->refclk / 2) / info->refclk;
81 *pfN = (*pfN - 4096) & 0xffff;
82 return freq;
83 }
84 }
85
86 if (unlikely(best_err == ~0)) {
87 nvkm_error(subdev, "unable to find matching pll values\n");
88 return -EINVAL;
89 }
90
91 return info->refclk * *pN / *pM / *P;
92}
